00:00:07,940 --> 00:00:11,900
to the principal engineer for another division

13
00:00:11,900 --> 00:00:15,359
and have them represent what we're trying to do

14
00:00:15,359 --> 00:00:17,120
and influence that person.

15
00:00:18,019 --> 00:00:21,260
Because often if I go talk to my peer, another VP,

16
00:00:21,260 --> 00:00:23,839
that VP says, well, maybe we could do that.

17
00:00:23,839 --> 00:00:25,800
What does my PE say?

18
00:00:25,800 --> 00:00:27,620
What does my advisor say?

19
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,600
And so I need to be able to send my advisor to their advisor.

20
00:00:02,600 --> 00:00:05,879
And picking senior engineers, it does matter

21
00:00:05,879 --> 00:00:08,800
that my advisor has the technical skill to be right,

22
00:00:09,679 --> 00:00:13,679
but it also matters that they have the social skill

23
00:00:13,679 --> 00:00:18,679
to go talk to the other engineer and convince them.

24
00:00:19,760 --> 00:00:23,120
And of course, sometimes it happens

25
00:00:23,120 --> 00:00:24,559
that when my principal engineer

26
00:00:24,559 --> 00:00:27,039
talks to their principal engineer,

27
00:00:27,039 --> 00:00:28,559
actually their principal engineer

28
